post_text:
Similar to the grab-and-go meals program offered at Union Community School District this past summer, enrolled students will be offered breakfast and lunch each day school is in session, free of charge, starting this coming Monday, September 14.

Although the regular school meals will be free of charge there will still be a charge for al a carte items at the middle and high school. Additionally, there will continue to be a charge for adult meals.

Further information will be forthcoming relative to students enrolled in remote learning.

The funding for this program is once again coming from USDA. The program will run through December 30, or until funds are depleted, whichever comes first.

KNIGHTS FANS AND VISITORS: We are excited to welcome you back to the football field this week as our Knights take on the Oelwein Huskies! Please keep in mind the following guidelines and restrictions that are in place for all of this year's home football events:

1) Masks are to be worn in the bleachers and anywhere else where social distancing cannot be maintained.
2) Only the Lower Concessions will be open, it will have limited options, all prepackaged.
3) All restroom facilities will be available
4) Admission is $5.00, exact change is preferred. If you are paying with a credit card, those will only be accepted at the main gate.

Did You Know?

1) As of today, August 6, 2020, 77.3% of La Porte City and 71.6% of Dysart residents; (70.1% of BH County and 65.7% of Tama County) have completed the Census form.

2) September 30th is the final day to be counted in the 2020 Census.

3) You can complete your Census form online at my2020census.gov; by phone 844-330-2020; or by mail using the form mailed to you in March.

Be that one person who makes a difference!

post_text:
The Department of Education has released new open enrollment guidance and an application in accordance with Senate File 2310. This law extends the open enrollment deadline for the 2020-21 school year to July 15 for parents, guardians and caregivers to apply to open enroll a student at an approved online public school in certain circumstances where the student, or a person who resides with the student, has a significant health condition that may increase the risk of Covid-19.

If you have further questions, please visit the Open Enrollment page on the district website.
shared_text:
UNION.K12.IA.US
Open Enrollment COVID-19 Update - Union Community School District
text:
The Department of Education has released new open enrollment guidance and an application in accordance with Senate File 2310. This law extends the open enrollment deadline for the 2020-21 school year to July 15 for parents, guardians and caregivers to apply to open enroll a student at an approved online public school in certain circumstances where the student, or a person who resides with the student, has a significant health condition that may increase the risk of Covid-19.

If you have further questions, please visit the Open Enrollment page on the district website.

Union CSD Parents/Guardians:

COVID-19 has made significant changes to our school and communities. This survey seeks to gain more information from our parents regarding the best way to support education for our students moving into the fall. Survey submissions are due no later than Friday, July 17th

Union CSD has been diligently working on a Return to Learn plan that gives the most information to students, parents and our community regarding our plans for returning to school in the fall. At this time, Union CSD is only planning for a return to in person learning or our virtual learning option if COVID-19 cases warrant a school building or district closure.

While we cannot foresee all the challenges that the fall will bring, we are hoping to use your responses to better plan for the fall return to school. Thank you for your time and support of our school district.

REMINDER:
Preschool registration packets will be available TODAY May 18, from 4 pm to 6 pm at the LPC Elementary and Dysart Elementary Preschool buildings. Please bring a birth certificate (or a photocopy), a current physical, and immunization card.

Registration materials will be distributed to families in a drive-by style. The packet will be handed to you through your vehicle‚Äôs window. You can pull over and complete the materials and then once you have finished there will be a tub available to drop them in. No one will be allowed to enter the buildings, and if you do exit your vehicle we remind you to practice required social-distancing.

For more information, contact Stephanie Estling s_estling@union.k12.ia.us (La Porte City) or Jamie Bernhards j_bernhards@union.k12.ia.us (Dysart).

Check the Union Community School District website at https://www.union.k12.ia.us/ for the fall formal online registration for all students including preschool through twelfth grade, the school start date, and Open House date.

Congratulations Sherry Parker! 2020 Gold Star Teacher!

On Thursday morning, April 23, during the Dysart-Geneseo staff meeting over Google Meet, Principal Mark Albertsen announced to everyone that Sherry Parker, second grade teacher at DG Elementary, had been named one of 10 Gold Star Teachers by the R.J. McElroy Trust and KWWL-TV. Sherry now joins the ranks of more than 300 teachers who have received this prestigious recognition since 1989.

Click the link below to read the full article -->
https://www.union.k12.ia.us/2020/04/2020-gold-star-teacher/

CONGRATULATIONS!
Teams of high school students from districts all over Iowa read 28 award winning books throughout the school year. Last week, students took an online test about the books. One of our UHS teams, composed of Rachel Hellman, Emma Deaton, and Dolores Cicio, finished 8th in the state. Congratulations to these girls for their great finish to a year's worth of hard work!

There has never been a more important time to fill out the US Census.

Iowa has moved to the #2 spot in the nation for US Census responses! We are now reporting at 55.4%. This is awesome news! Black Hawk County is reporting at 56.1%. Let's increase those numbers and help ensure our community will receive its fair share of federal funds, grants and support for local hospitals, first responders, health clinics and many other programs such as the school lunch program and services for needy families.

In times like this filling out the Census has never been more important. It's quick and simple. Click the link below and be counted! https://my2020census.gov/

post_text:
I would like to extend a grateful and heartfelt thank you to the communities of La Porte City and Dysart, for stepping up and joining in our efforts to provide meals for our students during the state-wide school closure for Corvid-19. Yvonna Krutzfeldt of Crosspointe Church in Dysart, along with Jeff and Angie Hutton of Heartland Church in La Porte City, were the guiding force behind the meal preparation and distribution March 23 through 25.

Another huge thank you needs to go out to Union‚Äôs Food Services Director Tina Hanna, who worked tirelessly for many days trying to get approval from the State of Iowa and USDA so that the Union district could prepare and provide the meals. She and her crew are now working to make sure the nutritional needs of our students are being met each day.

Without the continued support from our community‚Äôs we would not be able to provide the many opportunities for our students.

Travis Fleshner
Superintendent, Union Community Schools

post_text:
UPDATE: New USDA Guidance for Free Meals for Students

Due to newly-released USDA guidance, caregivers may pick up meals for children at Grab & Go meal sites effective immediately. This includes the sites at Union High School in La Porte City, and Union Middle School in Dysart.

USDA recognizes that in this public health emergency, continuing to require children to come to the meal site to pick up meals may not be practical and in keeping with the goal of providing meals while also taking appropriate safety measures. The Iowa Department of Education has submitted a plan to the USDA to ensure Program operators are able to maintain accountability and program integrity, and prevent duplication of meals served to any child.

Caregivers are to share the school name where each child attends that they are requesting meals for, if the children are of school age.

https://www.union.k12.ia.us/covid-19-info/

post_text:
The Union Music Department is proud to be a part of the Iowa High School Musical Theatre Awards program. Its sole purpose if to help us grow as performers finding paths for constant improvement. Professionals in the field of musical theatre attend our show and give us constructive feedback on every aspect of our show from the lobby feel, to the assistance with tickets, to lighting, costumes, hair, choreography, sound, the pit band, the audience support and most importantly character development and vocal abilities. It isn't a right or wrong program but rather a way for us to get new perspective and ways to take our skills to the next level. This video linked below uses parts of our production of "Joseph" last year.....check it out.

‚≠êÔ∏èYou don't want to miss our show this year, "Bright Star."

Mark Your Calendar: Important 2020 Census Dates
‚Ä¢ March 12-20: Initial invitations to respond online and by phone will be delivered by the U.S. Postal Service. Areas that are less likely to respond online will receive a paper questionnaire along with the invitation to respond online or over the phone.
‚Ä¢ March 16-24: Reminder letters will be delivered.
‚Ä¢ March 26-April 3: Reminder postcards will be delivered to households that have not responded.
‚Ä¢ April 8-16: Reminder letters and paper questionnaires will be delivered to remaining households that have not responded.
‚Ä¢ April 20-27: Final reminder postcards will be delivered to households that have not yet responded before census takers follow up in person.
‚Ä¢ May 13-July 31: If a household does not respond to any of the invitations, a census taker will follow up in person.
